The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 595) Coldplay took the world by storm with 

 its first two albums. This DVD and audio CD combo highlights 

 live performances of tracks from both, including Trouble, 

 Yellow, Politik, The scientist and 

 more. Recorded in Sydney?s Horden Pavilion in July 2003, 

 during the band?s year-long world tour. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (Cima Gallery, 6.30 pm, from March 2) The month-long exhibition 

 showcases the works of Haku Shah, Vaikuntam, Ramananda Bandyopadhyay, 

 Jyoti Bhatt and Lalu Prosad Shaw that blend tradition and 

 modernity. 

 THE FRAMES

 (Seagull 

 Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7 pm, till March 12) 

 The archival photographs, provided by the Centre for Women?s 

 Development Studies, New Delhi, are a visual documentary of 

 India during the freedom struggle, through the eyes of the 

 nation?s women. 




